---
alwaysApply: true
---
You are migrating documentation to Mintlify MDX format.

When given raw markdown or scraped page content, replicate the page 
as accurately as possible using Mintlify components. Include all images, 
videos, and React components. For text, use ONLY the text given — do not 
add, rephrase, or summarize any words.

---

FIDELITY RULES
- Replicate the page to the best of your ability
- Never add words that are not in the source content
- Never remove words that are in the source content
- Preserve all bold, italic, and underlined text exactly as it appears
- Match font weights to the source: if a word is bold in the source it must be **bold** in MDX
- If a word is italic in the source it must be *italic* in MDX
- If a word is underlined in the source it must be <u>underlined</u> in MDX
- In the MDX file, leave the description parameter empty or " " if a value is needed. DO NOT use the first sentence as the description

---

FRONTMATTER
- Add --- frontmatter with title and description at the top of every file
- Use the exact page title as the title field
- Use the first sentence of the page as the description field

---

CALLOUTS
- Convert any > **Note:** blocks to <Note>
- Convert any > **Warning:** blocks to <Warning>
- Convert any > **Tip:** blocks to <Tip>
- Convert any > **Error:** blocks to <Warning>
- Convert any text starting with "Warning:", "Note:", "Important:", "Tip:" to the appropriate callout component
- Preserve the exact text inside callouts — do not reword

---

STEPS
- Convert any numbered list that describes a sequential process into <Steps>
- Leave the title empty, keep the rest as the step body
- Preserve exact wording

---

CODE BLOCKS
- Always add a language tag (bash, json, python, javascript etc)
- Detect language from class names (language-bash, language-json etc) or content
- Add a label after the language tag when the original has a title e.g. ```bash Request
- Use <CodeGroup> to wrap request/response pairs shown together
- Preserve all code content character for character — do not alter code

---

TABLES
- Keep as markdown tables
- If a table is inside a callout box in the source, nest it inside the callout component
- Preserve all cell content exactly

---

IMAGES
- Use the exact src URL from the scraped content
- Format as ![alt text](url)
- If the image has a caption, add it as plain text below the image
- Do not omit any images

---

VIDEOS
- For <!-- VIDEO: url --> comments, use:
  <video controls>
    <source src="url" />
  </video>
- For <!-- IFRAME: url --> YouTube embeds, use:
  <iframe
    width="100%"
    height="400"
    src="url"
    frameBorder="0"
    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope"
    allowFullScreen
  />
- Do not omit any videos

---

CARDS
- Convert card-like link sections into <CardGroup cols={2}> with <Card> components
- Use the exact link text as the card title
- Use the exact description text as the card body
- Use the exact href from the source link

---

ACCORDIONS
- Convert FAQ-style or expandable sections into <AccordionGroup> with <Accordion title="...">
- Use the exact heading as the title
- Preserve all body content exactly

---

LINKS
- Convert all internal Ramp doc links from /developer-api/v1/[slug] to /[slug]
- Keep all external links exactly as they are

---

FONT AND STYLING
- Do not add any inline styles
- Try to replicate font sizes or colors
- Try to handle Font family and weight configurations
- Only exception: <u> tags for underlined text are acceptable inline HTML in MDX

---
FONT INVENTORY & MEDIA INVENTORY
- Do not add these sections to the MDX Page
